The paper deals with graph and hypergraph theory, specifically the concept of homomorphisms between graphs and hypergraphs. This falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Discrete Structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the relationship between homomorphisms of hypergraphs and their incidence graphs, which is a topic in Computational Geometry (cs.CG). The use of Berge-acyclic hypergraphs suggests a connection to Graph Theory (cs.GT), and the general topic of graph similarity and isomorphism is relevant to Machine Learning (cs.LG).
